  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed combinations. This package contains a ValidationResult whose generation activity is described only in narrative prose; the structured prov:wasGeneratedBy link to the corresponding simulation execution Activity is absent, constituting a broken provenance chain (W-EP-02).",
