      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-montecarlo-uq-runs-cou2",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/piv-shear-cfd-comparison-2024q4"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cou2-absolute-hemolysis-mrl5",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index validation — five operating points, Monte Carlo UQ, MRL-5 assessment",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-experimental-hemolysis",
      "description": "The hemolysis index (HI) was predicted using the power-law Giersiepen–Wurzinger model embedded in the CFD solver. Five operating points (3000–5000 RPM, 3–7 L/min) were simulated using the finalized mesh (18.4 M polyhedral cells, y+ < 1 throughout). Monte Carlo sampling (n = 2000) propagated uncertainty in blood viscosity (±8%), power-law exponent (±12%), and inlet velocity profile (±5%). Predicted HI values ranged from 0.0031 to 0.0087 g/100 L, all below the 0.01 g/100 L clinical threshold. The 95th-percentile upper bound reached 0.0094 g/100 L at the highest-stress operating point (5000 RPM / 3 L/min), remaining below threshold. Experimental HI measurements from the FDA generic pump loop (n = 6 replicates per operating point) were used as the reference. Normalized root-mean-square error across all five points was 9.3%, within the MRL-5 acceptance criterion of ≤ 15%. The simulation campaign was executed over a three-week period in Q4 2024 using the institutional HPC cluster (48-core nodes, OpenFOAM v2312). Results were reviewed by two independent CFD engineers and the biomedical lead before acceptance. Full run logs and mesh files are archived in the project repository under tag v3.2.1."
    }
  ],
